    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove VAT for listed building repair materials and work",
        "additional_details": "Owning a listed building can be costly due to the specialised materials, skilled labour, and regulatory requirements involved in their maintenance. Removing the VAT element of these costs would not only alleviate a significant financial burden for property owners, but would also help ensure that these architectural treasures continue to stand the test of time, benefiting communities, culture, tourism, and the environment.",
        "background": "We want the Government to remove the cost of VAT for building repairs on listed buildings. This should cover materials and labour.",
